Cloud Service Models:

There are 3 Cloud Service Models:

IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)
PaaS (Platform as a Service)
SaaS (Software as a Service)



1. IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)

What is IaaS?

IaaS provides virtual servers, storage, and networking. You are responsible for installing and managing the operating system and applications.



Simple Definition

AWS gives you the infrastructure, and you manage everything else.



Real-Life Example

Imagine renting an empty apartment.

The owner provides:

Building
Electricity
Water

You arrange:

Furniture
TV
Kitchen
Decorations

👉 Similarly, AWS provides the infrastructure, and you configure the rest.

AWS Examples
EC2
EBS
VPC
Elastic Load Balancer


Who Manages What?
AWS Manages	      You Manage
Hardware	        Operating System
Storage	          Applications
Networking	      Software
Virtualization   	Data


Easy Keyword

IaaS = Rent Infrastructure

==================================================================================================================================


2. PaaS (Platform as a Service)

What is PaaS?

PaaS provides a ready-to-use platform for developers. AWS manages the infrastructure and operating system, while you only deploy your application.



Simple Definition

AWS manages the infrastructure and OS. You only upload your application.



Real-Life Example

Imagine renting a fully furnished apartment.


The owner provides:

Furniture
Kitchen
Electricity
Internet

You simply move in and start living.

👉 Similarly, developers only upload their application.


AWS Examples
Elastic Beanstalk
AWS Lambda
AWS App Runner


Who Manages What?
AWS Manages	       You Manage
Hardware	         Application Code
Operating System	 Application Data
Runtime	
Storage	



Easy Keyword

PaaS = Ready Platform

============================================================================================================================================



3. SaaS (Software as a Service)


What is SaaS?

SaaS provides a complete software application over the internet. You don't install or manage anything—just sign in and use it.



Simple Definition

Everything is managed by the service provider. You simply use the software.



Real-Life Example

Using Gmail.



You don't manage:
Servers
Storage
Updates
Security

You just log in and send emails.


Examples
Gmail
Microsoft 365
Zoom
Dropbox
Salesforce


Who Manages What?
Provider Manages	    You Manage
Everything	          Your Data
Easy Keyword

SaaS = Ready Software
